text.section:
The Board shall include in each occupational safety and health standard that it proposes or recommends:
a requirement for the use of a label or other appropriate form of warning as necessary to ensure that each employee is apprised of:
each hazard to which the employee is exposed;
each relevant symptom of exposure;
emergency treatment appropriate for exposure; and
each proper condition and precaution for safe use or exposure;
when appropriate in connection with a hazard, a requirement for:
use of suitable protective equipment; and
control of technological procedures; and
as necessary to protect employees, a requirement to measure or monitor exposure of employees to a hazard:
at appropriate intervals;
at each appropriate location; and
in an appropriate manner.
